cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite it as below."
title: "Architecture Trumps the Operator: Architectural Verification Failure in Production LLM Workflows"
authors:
  - family-names: Ajitsaria
    given-names: Abhishek
    email: abhishek.ajitsaria@gmail.com
    city: Guwahati
    country: IN
type: dataset
date-released: 2026-04-14
repository-code: "https://github.com/abhishekajitsaria/11m-production-failure-case"
abstract: >-
  A single-user, production-scale case study documenting 119+ failures
  with zero self-corrections across 12+ Claude Max sessions over three
  weeks. Introduces the file-versus-response monitoring gap: a novel
  finding where comprehensive monitoring (93 checks) achieved 0% catch
  rate because it measured file properties while all failures occurred
  in conversational judgment. Includes three controlled experiments
  (guard suspension, guard reactivation/passivity trap, diagnostics
  declared permanent) and validation against 16 peer-reviewed sources.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - self-correction
  - AI safety
  - production failures
  - monitoring
  - verification
  - case study
license: CC-BY-4.0
